aa(lp42
VWhen I sat down to write a book about creativity,
p43
aVI realized that the steps were reversed.
p44
aVI had to let go at the very beginning, and I had to
p45
aVimmerse myself in the stories of hundreds of artists
p46
aVand writers and musicians and filmmakers, and as I listened
p47
aVto these stories, I realized that creativity
p48
aVgrows out of everyday experiences
p49
aVmore often than you might think, including
p50
aVletting go.
p51
aVIt was supposed to break, but that's okay. (Laughter) (Laughs)
p52
aVThat's part of the letting go, is sometimes it happens
p53
aVand sometimes it doesn't, because creativity also grows
p54
aVfrom the broken places.
