VThere's a fourth embrace, and it's the hardest.
p187
aVIt's the embrace of loss,
p188
aVthe oldest and most constant of human experiences.
p189
aVIn order to create, we have to stand in that space
p190
aVbetween what we see in the world and what we hope for,
p191
aVlooking squarely at rejection, at heartbreak,
p192
aVat war, at death.
